Nov 04 2015 11:00:17 PM UTC;michael.cahill;I think "bulk" should work purely as a hint to WiredTiger -- we should be free to ignore it.

To make that work with column stores, I think we should require "append" explicitly to get the current behavior.  If we can't support column store bulk loads without append (for now), they should silently ignore "bulk".

I checked "wt load" and was surprised to find that it doesn't use a bulk cursor.  It would need to check that there are no indexes for a table, but I suspect splitting out "append" from "bulk" would make bulk loads feasible for simple tables.  I guess a user could try to load an out-of-order dump, but that seems like a sufficiently special case that we could add a command line flag to disable bulk loads.;;;

